thread.title: MetLife Cements Legal Victory in Shedding ‘Systemically Important’ Label

author: Ryan Tracy
title: MetLife Cements Legal Victory in Shedding ‘Systemically Important’ Label

organizations.name: u.s. court of appeals for the district of columbia circuit

text:
WASHINGTON—The Trump administration ended the government’s appeal of a 2016 court decision that released MetLife Inc. from federal oversight, cementing a legal victory for the firm.
The large insurer and regulators on the U.S. Financial Stability Oversight Council jointly asked the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit to dismiss the case.
